Defendant James D Carlisle in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant ordered to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence with credit of 3 days time served, and with Huber Privileges for work.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 1 YEAR with the following conditions:

*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Mental health assessment with current treatment provided if applicable.
*Maintain absolute sobriety.  No illegal drugs.  No alcohol.
*Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
*Seek and maintain full time employment, job training and/or school.
*No frequenting places where illegal drugs or alcohol are used, sold or distrubuted. 

The Court orders defendant to pay  ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES during probation, or a CIVIL JUDGMENT shall be entered.  
 
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.

Pursuant to 973.015, Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a class H or I felony or a misdemeanor, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement.  Upon successful completion of the sentence.  Court will consider motion for expungement if defendant successfully completes sentence and has no further violations of the law.
